  "markup": "It has been said\u0026hellip;.we learn from our mistakes. Hopefully this is true. However, it is always better to learn from O.P.M. (Other People\u0027s Mistakes) \u0026nbsp;\nThis webinar is a collection of common PBM questions and protocol errors that we see in the clinical support department and when teaching PBM classes. \u0026nbsp;Examples-Treating through clothing, Over treating, Under treating and Mistreating. \u0026nbsp;Skipping around the Priority Principles, and playing laser treatment Hop Scotch so to speak. \u0026nbsp;The nice thing is, with PBM you are never going to hurt anyone with the wrong treatment\u0026hellip;but you really owe it to your patients your best. \u0026nbsp;\nThat is really what this webinar is about. \u0026nbsp;Join Dr. Chris Carraway, and special guest Dr. Elizabeth Starkey as they review the Do\u0026rsquo;s and Don\u0026rsquo;ts for good Laser Therapy."
}]]></Value>
